{"tid":598920,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"USTR ： five conditions for countries seeking exclusion","createTime":"2018-03-20T03:28:37.000Z","updateTime":"2018-03-21T01:56:08.000Z","uid":24140,"like":17,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":27,"replies":[{"pid":"6ae3217e6bb794c7f0d870e26ceb2b864faf9a9a","tid":598920,"uid":24140,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-03-20T03:28:37.000Z","msg":"The Trump administration is pressing countries to ally with the U.S. in pushing back against Chinese trade policies in exchange for relief from American tariffs on steel and aluminum, according to a European official.<br />\n<br />\nU.S. Trade Representative Robert Lighthizer has been leading negotiations under which countries may be excluded from the tariffs of 25 percent on imported steel and 10 percent on aluminum. American trading partners and U.S. companies are pressing for exemptions and exclusions from the tariffs, which take effect on Friday.<br />\n<br />\nIn talks with the U.S., Lighthizer has laid out five conditions that countries must address before being excluded, said the official, who spoke on condition of anonymity. The information was also contained in an internal European Commission document seen by Bloomberg. A second non-U.S. official confirmed the broad outlines of the five conditions.<br />\n<br />\nThe qualifications are:<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\">Limiting steel and aluminum exports to the U.S. to 2017 levels<br />\nActively addressing China&rsquo;s various trade-distorting policies<br />\nBeing more assertive and cooperative with the U.S. at the G-20 Global Steel Forum<br />\nCooperating with the U.S. in launching cases against Chinese practices at the WTO<br />\nEnhancing security cooperation with the U.S.<br />\n<br />\n</span><br />\nThe U.S. Trade Representative&rsquo;s office didn&rsquo;t immediately reply to a request for comment<br />\n<br />\n支那GG啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"064983695903b0986b2abb05263c317452ebd978","tid":598920,"uid":141151,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-03-20T03:30:25.000Z","msg":"U.S. Offers Trade Relief for Help in Pressuring China, Source Says<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-03-19/u-s-said-to-seek-alliance-against-china-in-tariff-relief-talks\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2018-03-19%2Fu-s-said-to-seek-alliance-against-china-in-tariff-relief-talks&d=D%2BverwI54%2FCFhfeffaWAvm6tz0R9Svbxs0EcWe5CwMI%3D&h=3818a928\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-03-19/u-s-said-to-seek-alliance-against-china-in-tariff-relief-talks</a><br />\n<br />\nLimiting steel and aluminum exports to the U.S. to 2017 levels<br />\nActively addressing China&rsquo;s various trade-distorting policies<br />\nBeing more assertive and cooperative with the U.S. at the G-20 Global Steel Forum<br />\nCooperating with the U.S. in launching cases against Chinese practices at the WTO<br />\nEnhancing security cooperation with the U.S.<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c7c2052735c618bda2621950303e0092dea22fec","tid":598920,"uid":4783,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-03-20T03:36:52.000Z","msg":"香港G9G<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/369.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"175a4ba3e1a20303a26d92b983bf6541ad2bf185","tid":598920,"uid":511,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-03-20T03:37:33.000Z","msg":"陳百祥召喚<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b19d51bfec6521732a0b489a5f35268906785336","tid":598920,"uid":2772,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"c7c2052735c618bda2621950303e0092dea22fec","tid":598920,"uid":4783,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-03-20T03:36:52.000Z","msg":"香港G9G<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/369.gif\" class=\"hkgmo